During a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Sean Spicer highlighted President Trump's recent achievements. These included the official approval of the Keystone XL pipeline and Charter Communications' commitment to invest $25 billion in the US and hire an additional 20,000 American workers. Spicer also discussed the ongoing vote on the American Health Care Act, emphasizing that the President has done everything possible to repeal and replace Obamacare. He stated that the President has made it clear that this is the time to fulfill the promise made to the American people. Spicer added that a collapse of the bill would not be ideal, but that it would also be a political cost to continue dragging out the process. He concluded by saying that regardless of the outcome, the President is committed to moving forward with tax reform.